               <p>JAMES EDWARD GROOM. I was in <placeName id="t18270913-258-crimeloc1458">St. Martin's-court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-258-crimeloc1458" type="placeName" value="St. Martin's-court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-258-crimeloc1458" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-258-off1456 t18270913-258-crimeloc1458"></join> between nine and ten o'clock on the 19th of August I had used my handkerchief a few minutes before - I heard a person call, "Stop that gentleman!" I stopped; put my hand to my pocket, and it was gone - I saw the prisoner in custody at the time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-258-person2115">
                  JOHN 
                  BOSTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2115" type="surname" value="BOSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2115" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2115" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in St. Martin's-court. I saw the prisoner and another lad - I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief from the gentleman's pocket; I called out, and took it from the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-258-person2116">
                  JOHN 
                  GROOM
               <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2116" type="surname" value="GROOM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2116" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-258-person2116" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I came up and saw Boston with the prisoner; he gave me this handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. This man came up, and said,"You have got that gentleman's handkerchief;" and he had it in his other hand at the time.</p>
               <p>
